Mexico Stocks: Chedraui, Soriana Advance; Penoles Declines

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-06-27T20:39:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/mexico-stocks-chedraui-advances-industrias-penoles-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.7 percent to 35,601.73. The exchange
halted trading twice during today’s session to address
sluggishness in its an operating system installed during the
weekend, Bolsa Mexicana de Valores SAB said in an e-mailed
statement.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SA (CHDRAUIB MM), the supermarket
chain based in Xalapa, Mexico, climbed 0.9 percent to 36.97
pesos. Chedraui was rated “overweight” in new coverage at HSBC
Holdings Plc, which cited its pace of expansion and “aggressive
pricing strategy,” according to an e-mailed research note.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, declined 0.6 percent to 433.06 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery fell for a third day, retreating
as much as 3.6 percent to $33.395 an ounce on the Comex in  New
York .  Organizacion Soriana SAB (SORIANAB MM), Mexico’s second-
largest grocery store chain, advanced 1.1 percent to 34.33
pesos. The company had its recommendation raised to “neutral”
from “underweight” at HSBC, which cited an improving consumer
environment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
